    "description": "<p>Monks are master martial artists that perfect their mind and&nbsp;bodies utilizing ebb and flow of their inner energy. They use&nbsp;their body as a weapon and can enter into different stances&nbsp;that drastically change their combat abilities.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source of Power:</strong></em> Monks have become enlightened and are aware and in touch with their inner Ki energy to hone their bodies and minds. Their journey to become a Monk could be from being trained in a monastery, mentored by a mysterious figure, or their own deep meditation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Starting Equipment</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>2 Light Weapon</li>\n<li>3 Throwing Weapons</li>\n<li>1 set of Novice Light Armor</li>\n<li>X or Y &ldquo;Packs&rdquo; (Adventuring Packs Coming Soon)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Monk Martial Mastery</h2>\n<p><strong>Combat Masteries:</strong> Light Weapons &amp; Light Armor</p>\n<p><strong>Maneuvers &amp; Weapon Passives: </strong>You gain access to all&nbsp;Maneuvers and Weapon Style Passives.</p>\n<p><strong>Techniques Known:</strong> You learn a number of Techniques&nbsp;as shown in the Techniques Known column of the Monk&nbsp;Class Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Stamina Points:</strong> You have a maximum number of Stamina&nbsp;Points as shown in the Stamina Points column of the Monk&nbsp;Class Table.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Class Table</h2>\n<table style=\"border-width: 2px; border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col><col><col><col><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Level&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Bonus HP</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Attribute Points</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Skill Points</strong></td>\n<td sty